cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on face hallucination, which is a computer vision task related to image processing and computer graphics. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a novel Super-Identity Convolutional Neural Network (SICNN) to recover identity information for generating faces closed to the real identity. This involves training a neural network to learn a robust identity metric for faces from two domains (high-resolution and hallucination domains). Therefore, the paper also involves machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves image and video processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves training a neural network, which can be considered as an optimization problem, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category.
